headline: Why Baxter (BAX) Stock Is Trading Lower Today
summary: Shares of healthcare company Baxter International (NYSE:BAX) fell 4.5% in the afternoon session after Barclays lowered its price target on the stock to $30 from $36, signaling a more cautious outlook on the company.
